[SN]TITLE[SN]
US presidential candidates weigh in on Iran deal

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
News of a deal on Iran's nuclear programme has sparked a surge of opinions on social media across the globe. Most of the 2016 candidates for the White House - both Democrat and Republican - took to Twitter on Tuesday to weigh in on the historic pact.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
*As of Tuesday afternoon, Republicans Rand Paul and Donald Trump did not address the Iran deal on their Twitter accounts. On CNN, Mr Trump said "Iran is laughing at us" over the deal. Democrats Hillary Clinton and Martin O'Malley also did not release statements on Twitter. However, Mrs Clinton told reporters on Tuesday that the deal was an "important step in putting the lid on Iran's nuclear programme".
